Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.53,0:00:16.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Let's adjust the suspension.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.59,0:00:19.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.38,0:00:22.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,With this, the interlocking is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.56,0:00:24.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.21,0:00:27.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, you've got an incredible fleet here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.88,0:00:31.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for informing us about the pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.89,0:00:33.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're welcome here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.13,0:00:34.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.07,0:00:36.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know we're in good hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.82,0:00:43.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander, the interlocking \Nprocess is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.06,0:00:45.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. And what about {\i1}him{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.02,0:00:47.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.99,0:02:21.99,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,The Flute of Recollection
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.03,0:02:27.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Tighten the wire!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.93,0:02:34.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chief! That's in the way! Move it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.54,0:02:36.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You don't just set it down \Nwherever you feel like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.72,0:02:39.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where... to move it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.68,0:02:42.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.00,0:02:44.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See? By the other cargo!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.64,0:02:47.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Move it over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.77,0:02:48.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.13,0:02:55.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.57,0:02:58.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you not to fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.61,0:03:05.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Chamber!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.15,0:03:08.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you alright?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.77,0:03:13.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot! Don't cut that rope!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.65,0:03:15.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Can you get yourself out of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.36,0:03:26.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't decided how to handle \Nyour right of residence yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.10,0:03:30.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So if you don't mind, please use \Nthis area as your quarters for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.75,0:03:32.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.53,0:03:33.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a problem with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.88,0:03:35.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This place is a dump!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.74,0:03:37.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This... is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.76,0:03:41.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber... nearby. Convenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.32,0:03:42.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all you care about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.93,0:03:44.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.76,0:03:47.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And one more thing. Here's your invoice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.67,0:03:49.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In...voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.14,0:03:54.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A demand to pay for damages incurred \Nto the hangar while rendering service.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.99,0:03:59.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second, Ridget! Ledo is the \None who drove the pirates away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.85,0:04:02.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The destruction of the hangar \Nhas nothing to do with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.98,0:04:06.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But Ledo just got here! \NHe doesn't know the rules!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.21,0:04:10.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're exempting him from electricity \Nexpended while staying here, water fee,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.83,0:04:16.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and the freight charge of hauling \Nthis oversized cargo around.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.71,0:04:19.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's not just a one-sided deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.61,0:04:22.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo! Are you okay with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.88,0:04:27.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Query: What is the specific \Nnature of this "deal"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.37,0:04:33.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! This Yunboro's in the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.16,0:04:34.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Move... where?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.87,0:04:38.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For cryin' out loud... Get the next load.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.52,0:04:40.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Put it in the same place as before!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.29,0:04:43.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber, move it over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.05,0:04:43.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.82,0:04:47.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop flying, dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.39,0:04:50.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's an impressive Yunboro...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.83,0:04:54.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it understand when other \Npeople besides you talk to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.40,0:04:55.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Understands...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.47,0:04:57.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it do what I say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.07,0:05:02.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Based on the allowable \Nscope of military protocol,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.40,0:05:04.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,it is possible to transfer command authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.86,0:05:05.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.98,0:05:07.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.21,0:05:09.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Alright...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.19,0:05:13.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chief! I got a good idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.19,0:05:17.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.10,0:05:25.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Delivery for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.36,0:05:26.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.94,0:05:31.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's working hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.61,0:05:36.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.84,0:05:42.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell's his deal? He makes the tin \Ncan do all the work while he slacks off!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.45,0:05:43.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.82,0:05:47.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a dimwit if I ever saw one! Like I \Nsaid before, he should just be deep-sixed...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.72,0:05:51.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He might be just taking a break, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.54,0:06:00.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the way to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.68,0:06:05.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I fail to see any meaning in your behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.10,0:06:08.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing more than a meditation tool.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.15,0:06:15.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, hot as it is, they're \Nsure wasting a lot of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.21,0:06:19.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no discipline at all here. \NWhat's their instructor doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.85,0:06:24.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conjecture: Children's drills \Nhere do not have an instructor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.16,0:06:27.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how can they be raised as \Nproductive members of society?   {I added "productive"}{smp: considering the stated intention of the show creators that this is a metaphor about 20-somethings at a loss to integrate into the real world, i think use of the english cliche phrase is the right choice.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.21,0:06:30.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Query: What is the next order?  {double-check "query" is okay? couldn't find it or variant in previous eps} {smp: I couldn't find anything either. I like Query.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.24,0:06:31.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.45,0:06:33.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm first!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.19,0:06:34.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.14,0:06:35.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Say something!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.62,0:06:36.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fly up to the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.85,0:06:41.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Obstructions prevent completion of duties. \NQuery: Permission to clear them away?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.44,0:06:45.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Granted. But take care not to hurt anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.09,0:06:46.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.24,0:06:50.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.79,0:06:52.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How's it going?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.09,0:06:53.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Standing by...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.70,0:06:56.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Standing by"? Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.82,0:07:00.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that? Are you making something?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.35,0:07:02.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I... don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.95,0:07:06.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're making something but you don't \Nknow what it is? How strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.23,0:07:09.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's an unusual material.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.04,0:07:12.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hideauze nail. No have... on this planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.30,0:07:17.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.01,0:07:19.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want... I give.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.88,0:07:21.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.98,0:07:28.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, would you like to take \Na little walk with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.04,0:07:34.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This'll be a great souvenir \Nfor my little brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.44,0:07:35.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Little... brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.70,0:07:40.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh. His name's Bebel. He's \Nreally good working with his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.71,0:07:43.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What does "little brother" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.73,0:07:49.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Little brother" is a brother \Nwho's younger than you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.29,0:07:51.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... in your family...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.90,0:07:53.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fam...ily...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.02,0:07:54.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In ancient society,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.67,0:08:00.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,that label was applied to societal units \Ncomprised of mates and blood relations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.27,0:08:03.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They had that custom?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.08,0:08:06.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have a family, Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.52,0:08:09.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Inefficient. Unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.09,0:08:11.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Inefficient...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.11,0:08:14.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like you lived \Nin a rough place, Ledo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.63,0:08:20.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bebel wants to ask you about space.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.11,0:08:21.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,About... space?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.93,0:08:27.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. He's really interested in the stars and \Nvehicles you use to travel through space.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.51,0:08:33.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But his body is weak, so he \Ncan't walk around as he likes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.40,0:08:35.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Body... is weak?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.61,0:08:38.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's got like a disease... in the chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.41,0:08:44.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In the Galactic Alliance, frail humans \Nare eliminated and disposed of.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.33,0:08:48.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Humans who cannot participate \Nin battle are useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.15,0:08:53.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Useless! That's... Ledo, \Nwere you okay with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.00,0:08:56.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't... understand... question.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.89,0:08:58.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.28,0:09:04.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Will I be able to gain useful \Ninformation by talking to that person?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.65,0:09:06.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Information?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.14,0:09:10.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, why not meet Dr. Oldham?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.08,0:09:11.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Old...ham...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.22,0:09:15.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a doctor, but people \Ncall him "the Sage".  {don't know why there's a "five" in the Japanese; typo, "go" as honorific instead of "go" = "five"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.75,0:09:18.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the smartest person in all of Gargantia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.31,0:09:33.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.28,0:09:45.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello! Dr. Oldham!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.03,0:09:46.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.83,0:09:49.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor, Amy's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.11,0:09:50.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.89,0:09:51.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.81,0:09:53.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, Amy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.24,0:09:56.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought someone here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.08,0:10:01.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that you're Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.28,0:10:04.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He says he's got something \Nto ask you, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.43,0:10:09.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I've still got work \Nto do, so I'm taking off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.69,0:10:11.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're busy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.92,0:10:15.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo, I'll come by to pick you \Nup later, so wait downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.97,0:10:25.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like you to provide information.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.98,0:10:29.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard the rumors,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.32,0:10:32.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but is that the voice of the \Nmachine that can understand words?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.59,0:10:34.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That... is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.14,0:10:39.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lost technology. I never imagined I'd be \Nable to lay my eyes on the real thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.17,0:10:42.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I... ask question?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.40,0:10:44.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, although I'm not sure I'll know the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.16,0:10:46.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, sit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.10,0:10:51.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want to ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.19,0:10:56.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I would ask about how to return \Nto the Galactic Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.70,0:11:01.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid I don't possess any \Nknowledge pertaining to that subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.01,0:11:06.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, we've lost the \Nmajority of ancient wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.66,0:11:10.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Particularly regarding the technology \Nof traveling to the stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:15.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Currently, this is the knowledge of \Nthe heavens that's been left to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.75,0:11:18.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt this is what you're looking for...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.92,0:11:22.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for being of no help.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.18,0:11:23.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It... can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.72,0:11:28.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I ask... one more question?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.62,0:11:30.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly, go right ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.26,0:11:35.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I would ask for your explanation \Nof the structure of this fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.31,0:11:36.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Explanation?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.54,0:11:41.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This fleet is inefficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.83,0:11:44.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The chain of command and training \Nof children are defective,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.39,0:11:47.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,while the behavior of the \Ncitizenry is disorganized.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.49,0:11:51.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And I cannot comprehend the \Npurpose of caring for the weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.66,0:11:58.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's how it looks \Nto a visitor from the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.59,0:12:00.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg your pardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.69,0:12:05.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This efficiency that you speak \Nof has a rather narrow range.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.07,0:12:10.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... I think you should meet Bebel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.10,0:12:16.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Will I attain any useful information \Nby conversing with that person?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.78,0:12:20.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether it's useful or not \Nis up to you to decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.80,0:12:35.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So even the doctor didn't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.23,0:12:39.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bebel! I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.12,0:12:41.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.69,0:12:53.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.92,0:12:56.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He really is your friend, Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.54,0:12:59.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're awesome, Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.40,0:13:02.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you. I'm Bebel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.88,0:13:04.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to... meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.92,0:13:08.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Amy's "little brother"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.51,0:13:12.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sit down, if you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.35,0:13:15.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo said he wanted to meet you, Bebel!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.54,0:13:16.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.80,0:13:18.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's... right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.29,0:13:23.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like you to provide information.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.68,0:13:25.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.33,0:13:28.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh! This is Chamber's \Ncommunications device.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.26,0:13:31.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! It really can talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.05,0:13:32.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.76,0:13:37.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am an artificial intelligence \Ncreated to aid my pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.15,0:13:41.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool! You understand Earth language, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.21,0:13:43.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy, are you in there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.47,0:13:45.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have enough people, \Nso we need your help...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.90,0:13:46.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.95,0:13:48.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? The hottie?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.64,0:13:50.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Already inviting him home?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.67,0:13:52.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.80,0:13:55.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I have to work again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.14,0:13:56.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.34,0:13:58.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just when it was getting good...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.57,0:14:00.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When {\i1}what{\i0} was getting good?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.46,0:14:02.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, it's nothing like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.36,0:14:04.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Bebel, take care of Ledo, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.68,0:14:06.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be in such a rush that you trip!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.67,0:14:08.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.11,0:14:09.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.15,0:14:11.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, my sister never stops moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.74,0:14:13.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I... don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.54,0:14:16.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo, are you really from space?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.21,0:14:20.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always wondered!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.40,0:14:24.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's life like in space?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.12,0:14:29.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,With the Galactic Alliance, the main \Nmission is fighting the Hideauze.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.74,0:14:31.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hideauze...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.48,0:14:36.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,An alien life-form that threatens \Nthe existence of the human race.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.88,0:14:38.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you always been fighting them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.74,0:14:45.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The war has been going on since the \Nformation of the Galactic Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.52,0:14:46.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.71,0:14:50.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be totally different \Nfrom how life is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.13,0:14:52.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it wear you out?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.74,0:14:56.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The only exhausted people are dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.36,0:15:02.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dead... I see. It's rough, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.69,0:15:06.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you used to things here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.27,0:15:14.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot comprehend the organizational \Nstructure of Gargantia.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.41,0:15:15.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Organization?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.73,0:15:21.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Query: What is the reason for running such \Nan inefficient and useless operation?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.24,0:15:28.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The fleet isn't an organization. \NIt's just everyone coming together.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.05,0:15:32.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes we fight, sometimes help each \Nother... And that's just how we live.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.36,0:15:35.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Query: What is the significance of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.46,0:15:40.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as everyone can live free \Nof worry, that's all that matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.97,0:15:43.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer is unclear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.57,0:15:48.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The behavioral objective of the human race \Nis subjugating the enemy, the Hideauze.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.73,0:15:52.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Without that, the human race \Nhas no stable development.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.18,0:15:53.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.54,0:15:59.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Humans like you are culled immediately \Nby the Galactic Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.38,0:16:00.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Culled...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.37,0:16:05.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But if that's the case, what would \Nbecome of the Galactic Alliance
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.60,0:16:07.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,if the Hideauze are beaten completely?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.59,0:16:10.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do, Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.82,0:16:15.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I would stand by until I \Nreceive further instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.30,0:16:18.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what if those instructions don't come?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.59,0:16:21.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I will just continue to stand by.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.13,0:16:25.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're the same as us, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.04,0:16:27.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Same?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.29,0:16:32.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, "standing by" means \Ncontinuing to live, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.03,0:16:44.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo, I heard Joe took your Yunboro away?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.62,0:16:47.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a shame, the hero being sidelined.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.54,0:16:50.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.60,0:16:54.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Query: Are my actions beneficial?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.75,0:16:56.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yours, Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.58,0:17:00.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You routed the pirates, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.13,0:17:06.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, all I am doing \Nis observing Chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.87,0:17:08.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just not used to it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.15,0:17:13.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am unable to determine \Nmy own course of action.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.45,0:17:16.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Course of action, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.14,0:17:19.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, why don't you knock off \Nthat kind of military-style thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.80,0:17:21.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Knock... off?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.06,0:17:24.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Be more flexible with...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.72,0:17:28.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.63,0:17:30.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Collect the rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.70,0:17:31.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?! What's happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.98,0:17:34.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Weather phenomena. It is not poisonous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.51,0:17:38.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an emergency situation! \NHave your Yunboro gather the rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.40,0:17:40.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fresh water is precious!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.41,0:17:41.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What... should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.77,0:17:44.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a tarp over there! Spread \Nit out to collect the water!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.63,0:17:46.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.58,0:17:48.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.21,0:18:29.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! Just like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.86,0:18:34.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a change in your brainwaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.47,0:18:38.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just wondering about how \Nour side is doing in the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.37,0:18:41.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Given the present circumstances, \Nsuch consideration is meaningless.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.15,0:18:43.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.59,0:18:45.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I spy the handsome guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.49,0:18:47.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He really is good-looking...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.64,0:18:53.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I kind of feel sorry for him, all \Nalone in a place he knows nothing about...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.86,0:18:56.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell, he'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.41,0:18:57.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.33,0:19:01.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're worried about him, \Naren't you?! Get over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.11,0:19:05.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.43,0:19:09.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're soaked. You're gonna catch a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.62,0:19:11.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dry off at my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.53,0:19:17.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure seems like it was some squall.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.01,0:19:20.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That was my first observation \Nof concentrated rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.66,0:19:23.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there rain in space, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.59,0:19:24.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.45,0:19:25.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are there oceans?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.29,0:19:26.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.24,0:19:29.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And people who are sick, like me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.28,0:19:31.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do not exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.97,0:19:36.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't think of myself as unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.62,0:19:39.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.36,0:19:42.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have my big sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.37,0:19:43.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.46,0:19:46.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My sister needs me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.38,0:19:52.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody must need you, too, Ledo. That's \Nwhy you've been able to survive all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.09,0:20:00.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In the war, only those who can be \Nof service are needed to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.79,0:20:06.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about the opposite? Isn't \Nthere someone whom you need, Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.57,0:20:10.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My sister and I need each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.13,0:20:15.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And more than anything, I need myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.14,0:20:17.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.44,0:20:18.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.22,0:20:24.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To the Alliance, a useful existence \Nhas no attachment to survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.25,0:20:27.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what was this to you, Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.67,0:20:28.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.58,0:20:34.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis told me you were making it, \Nbut didn't know what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.83,0:20:37.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This has to be a flute, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.95,0:20:40.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not necessary at all for war.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.51,0:20:41.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Flu...te...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.31,0:20:45.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It can produce a sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.52,0:21:06.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.78,0:21:08.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.83,0:21:10.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.36,0:21:12.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I say something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.50,0:21:15.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I... don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.17,0:21:17.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.19,0:21:21.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You must have recalled something sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.93,0:21:24.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... really?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.91,0:21:25.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bebel...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.77,0:21:26.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.64,0:21:28.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I... want that... one more time...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.43,0:21:30.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.80,0:21:39.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I made some tea!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.45,0:21:42.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Saaya's recommendation. It's good!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.38,0:21:52.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber, you still don't \Nknow our coordinates?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.53,0:21:56.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lack of observational data. \NMore time is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.10,0:21:57.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.53,0:22:01.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like I need to learn a \Nlittle more about this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.83,0:22:06.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unnecessary. Eventually, you \Nwill rejoin the main unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.29,0:22:09.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I know.
